.SH "NAME"
MIME::Decoder::QuotedPrint \- encode/decode a "quoted\-printable" stream
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
A generic decoder object; see MIME::Decoder for usage.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
A MIME::Decoder subclass for the \f(CW"quoted\-printable"\fR encoding.
The name was chosen to jibe with the pre-existing MIME::QuotedPrint
utility package, which this class actually uses to translate each line.
.IP "\(bu" 4
The \fBdecoder\fR does a line-by-line translation from input to output.
.IP "\(bu" 4
The \fBencoder\fR does a line-by-line translation, breaking lines
so that they fall under the standard 76\-character limit for this
encoding.
.PP
\&\fBNote:\fR just like MIME::QuotedPrint, we currently use the
native \f(CW"\en"\fR for line breaks, and not \f(CW\*(C`CRLF\*(C'\fR.  This may
need to change in future versions.
